Package arcade.patch.agent.cell

Class PatchCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.patch.agent.cell.PatchCell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cell, java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PatchCellCART, PatchCellRandom, PatchCellTissue
    public abstract class PatchCell
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cell
    Implementation of Cell for generic cell agent.

    Cells that become necrotic or senescent have a change to become apoptotic instead ( NECROTIC_FRACTION and SENESCENT_FRACTION, respectively).

    Cell parameters are tracked using a map between the parameter name and value. Daughter cell parameter values are drawn from a distribution centered on the parent cell parameter with the specified amount of heterogeneity (HETEROGENEITY).

    • Constructor Detail

      • PatchCell

        public PatchCell​(PatchCellContainer container,
                 Location location,
                 Parameters parameters,
                 GrabBag links)
        Creates a PatchCell agent.

        Loaded parameters include:

        • NECROTIC_FRACTION = fraction of necrotic cells that become apoptotic
        • SENESCENT_FRACTION = fraction of senescent cells that become apoptotic
        • ENERGY_THRESHOLD = maximum energy deficit before necrosis
        Parameters:
        container - the cell container
        location - the Location of the cell
        parameters - the cell parameters
        links - the map of population links

      • selectBestLocation

        public PatchLocation selectBestLocation​(Simulation sim,
                                        ec.util.MersenneTwisterFast random)
        Selects best location for a cell to be added or move into.

        Each free location is scored based on glucose availability and distance from the center of the simulation.

        Parameters:
        sim - the simulation instance
        random - the random number generator
        Returns:
        the best location or null if no valid locations

      • checkLocation

        static boolean checkLocation​(Simulation sim,
                             PatchLocation loc,
                             double addedVolume,
                             double maxHeight,
                             int population,
                             int maxDensity)
        Determine if a patch location is free.

        A location is free if the proposed cell volume can fit in the location without exceeding the max volume of a location, exceeding constituents' critical heights, and exceeding the population density is below the maximum.

        Parameters:
        sim - the simulation instance
        loc - the location
        addedVolume - the volume added to the location
        maxHeight - the maximum height tolerance
        population - the population index
        maxDensity - the maximum density of population in the location
        Returns:
        if the location is available for the cell
